This paper is primarily focused on entity resolution, which is a core problem in data integration and data cleaning. This problem is typically studied in the context of databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper proposes a hybrid human-machine approach to entity resolution, which involves using crowdsourcing platforms to bring human insight into the process. This approach involves designing efficient algorithms for generating batches of verification tasks, which is a problem that is closely related to optimization and machine learning (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of designing a user interface that is intuitive and easy to use for human workers, which is a topic that falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on real data sets, which involves analyzing and processing large amounts of data, a topic that is relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
